  "story": {
    "intro": [
      "The last greenhouse ark drifts toward a dead star, carrying every seed we have left.",
      "You are Pip, a pod-ship grown from the stubbornest seed in the vault. Roots in. Petals out.",
      "A meteor bloom has woken the chitin swarm. Keep the ark's glass unbroken all the way down."
    ],
    "levelIntros": [
      "SEEDLING SHALLOWS: The swarm sends its smallest first. Pop them gently. Or not gently.",
      "THE POLLEN DRIFT: Meteors thick as spring pollen. The ark sneezes. Stay close to it.",
      "THORN GATE: The brood-hive coils around the dead star. Every thorn is pointed at you."
    ],
    "bossIntro": "BARON THORNWAKE unfurls, a hive grown around a stolen sapling. He thinks gardens waste good light. Prove him wrong.",
    "victory": [
      "The seed takes. Green threads race across the dead star's crust like dawn learning to run.",
      "The ark opens every window. Somewhere inside, the keeper waters a fern and cries a little."
    ],
    "defeat": [
      "The ark drifts dark and quiet. But a pod-ship is a seed, and seeds are patient. Again.",
      "Thornwake laughs in spores. Let him. Spring has never once lost an argument with winter."
    ]
  },
